<br>
The answer to the puzzle is that you wouldn't see anything. At lightspeed time effectively stops. Anything under lightspeed for your car is fine though. Even if it's 99.99999% lightspeed. You see the beams fly off at lightspeed. In reality they are only travelling 0.00001% faster than you but because time has slowed for car and passenger it is a lot faster. No matter who observes those headlights, they are seen to be going at lightspeed. Lightspeed is a genuine barrier. The good news is that time dilation allows you to go anywhere. If Starships capable of near light velocities were commonplace then we could rapidly expand across the Galaxy. Trip times would be short for passengers. Those who choose to explore the stars could visit thousands of worlds in their lifetimes but mother Earth might be gone by the time they returned. Trips to local stars wouldn't be a problem. Visitors might return home every few centuries or less. Those with a yearning to reach the other side of the Galaxy might not see Earth again for 50,000 years or more. Even if from their perspective they were only gone 10 years and visited a dozen different Stars on a different spiral arm.<br>
<br>
Sounds lonely to return to a changed Earth but you wouldn't be completely alienated by a futuristic society on homecoming. There would be other explorers there on stopover or retired. How big a community exists depends on how many starships are plying the spaceways. I kind of like the idea of speeding over to Alpha Centaurii in a few hours, then covering the distance to the Galactic centre in similar time, then meeting up with other travellers in another spiral arm. The Earth would only be one World of many you could visit. There may be large numbers of Planets out there more hospitable than Earth. I might even settle down on one. I like solitude and the idea of my own quiet Planet would be tempting.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=drcarstairs>DrCarstairs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Utterly Mad Scientist</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/14/02 7:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.imgstudio.com/2002/March/28/stamp_lthumb/032820021216063.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Relativity</span><hr size=1> <br>
