<br>
It would be possible to explore other galaxies such as Andromeda but the 'real' time passing as viewed by those left behind on Earth would be staggering. The number of millenia that would pass each second of what might be only a 5 minute flight for the travellers would be astounding. Earth society would be as changed as ours is from Australopithecus. On your return trip you might meet thousands of other travellers from all periods of space history. Including your own. The meetings between different ships from different times would have had strange repurcussions since your intergalactic jaunt. Twentieth century humans with Fiftieth century technology. Sixtieth century humans wearing baseball caps and chewing bubble gum they traded for. Just as the nations of Earth exchange and reinvent customs the societies of the future, stretched across infinity will choose their own paths. <br>
